    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-04T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-04T01:00:00-05:00" n="772"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 C 353/199: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-04T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 4, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 4—8:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Following from American Consul [General], Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 3, noon. Consul <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CCB1"
                                >Chamberlain</persName>, on the way to the station <pb facs="0827"
                                n="729" xml:id="pg_729"/> in my car at 6:30 a.m., was stopped by
                            three Japanese soldiers who, after he had identified himself by card and
                            passport, without justification attacked him, striking him in the face
                            many times. Face badly bruised but otherwise uninjured. Incident
                            verbally reported to Japanese Consulate General with the request that
                            severe penalty be meted out.</p>
                        <p>
                            <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CCB1">Chamberlain</persName> will leave
                            for Harbin this afternoon.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Legation has brought the foregoing orally to the attention of the Japanese Chargé
                    d’Affaires here and is requesting <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMS1"
                        >Myers</persName> to report result of his representation.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
